Triage

Gives priority to a healing move.

Affected Moves

The following moves receive priority.

Name Type Category PP Power Accuracy Description
Absorb 25 30 100 A nutrient-draining attack. The user's HP is restored by half the damage taken by the target.
Bitter Blade 10 90 100 A bitter slash that restores the user's HP by half the damage taken by the target
Bouncy Bubble 15 90 100 An attack that absorbs half the damage inflicted.
Drain Punch 10 75 100 An energy-draining punch. The user's HP is restored by half the damage taken by the target.
Draining Kiss 10 50 100 The user steals the target's HP with a kiss, restoring its HP by over half of the damage dealt.
Dream Eater 15 100 100 The user eats the dreams of a sleeping target, restoring its HP by half the damage caused.
Endothermia 15 75 90 The user absorbs thermal energy, restoring its HP by half of the damage caused.
Floral Healing 10 — — The user restores the target's HP by up to half of its max HP. It restores more HP on grass.
Giga Drain 10 75 100 A nutrient-draining attack. The user's HP is restored by half the damage taken by the target.
Heal Order 10 — — The user calls out its underlings to heal it, regaining up to half of its max HP.
Heal Pulse 10 — — The user emits a healing pulse that restores the target's HP by up to half of its max HP.
Healing Wish 10 — — The user faints, but whoever takes its place will have its HP restored and status cured.
Horn Leech 10 75 100 The user's horns drain the target's energy, restoring its HP by half the damage dealt.
Jungle Healing 10 — — The user restores HP and cures any status conditions of itself and its ally Pokémon in battle.
Leech Life 10 80 100 The user drains the target's blood. The user's HP is restored by half the damage caused.
Life Dew 10 — — The user scatters mysterious water around, restoring the HP of itself and its ally Pokémon.
Lunar Blessing 10 0 — Restores HP and cures status conditions for itself and an ally.
Lunar Dance 10 — — The user faints, but whoever takes its place will have its HP restored and status cured.
Mana Sap 10 — 100 The user drains the target's Sp. Atk stat, restoring its HP but having its own Sp. Atk stat fall.
Matcha Gotcha 15 80 90
Mega Drain 15 55 100 A nutrient-draining attack. The user's HP is restored by half the damage taken by the target.
Milk Drink 10 — — The user restores its own HP by up to half of its max HP.
Moonlight 5 — — The user restores its own HP. The amount of HP regained varies with the weather.
Morning Sun 5 — — The user restores its own HP. The amount of HP regained varies with the weather.
Oblivion Wing 10 80 100 The user absorbs its target's HP, restoring its HP by over half of the damage caused.
Oxidize 5 — — The user restores its own HP. The amount of HP regained varies with the weather.
Parabolic Charge 20 65 100 The user attacks everything around it, restoring its HP by half the damage caused.
Parasitic Pulse 10 80 100 Parasites siphon the foe's energy to restore HP by half the damage caused.
Predation 10 60 100 The user feasts on the target's flesh, restoring its HP by half the damage caused.
Purify 20 — 100 The user heals the target's status condition and the user's own HP if successful.
Recover 10 — — Restoring its own cells, the user restores its own HP by half of its max HP.
Rest 10 — — The user sleeps for two turns, fully restoring its HP and healing any status conditions.
Revival Blessing 1 0 100 The user bestows a loving blessing to revive a fainted party {POKEMON} to half of its HP.
Roost 10 — — The user lands and rests its body. This restores its HP by up to half of its max HP.
Shore Up 10 — — The user regains up to half of its max HP. It restores more HP in a sandstorm.
Slack Off 10 — 100 The user slacks off, restoring its own HP by up to half of its max HP.
Soft-Boiled 10 — 100 The user restores its own HP by up to half of its max HP.
Spirit Sever 10 85 95 The user siphons the target's spirit, restoring its HP by half of the damage caused.
Strength Sap 10 — 100 The user restores its HP by the same amount as the target's Attack stat and lowers it.
Swallow 10 — — The power stored using the move Stockpile is absorbed by the user to heal its HP.
Synthesis 5 — — The user restores its own HP. The amount of HP regained varies with the weather.
Wish 10 — 100 In one turn, the user's or its replacement's HP is restored by half the user's max HP.
